( Recipe 👇🏻) This Shaved Brussel Sprouts Salad is the perfect way to get ready for holiday cooking. I’m using the freshest ingredients from my local @fredmeyerstores store to create this salad. #ad
.
Fred Meyer has everything you need to create your holiday spread, from dinnerware and decor to fresh seasonal ingredients to get your holiday cooking done. I love making sure my family has a big bowl of salad on our holiday table, so I’m sharing a favorite recipe with you. The best way to use up all the seasonal ingredients Fred Meyer has to offer at an affordable price.
.
Shaved Brussel Sprouts Salad
1 ¼ pound brussel sprouts, shaved
1 shallot, finely sliced
½ Opal apple, sliced
½ Pink Lady apple, sliced
½ pomegranite, seeded
8 slices bacon, cooked
¼ cup parmesan cheese, shaved
¼ cup pecans, chopped
Lemon Terragon Dressing
¼ cup tarragon, finely chopped
1 tablespoon stone ground mustard
½ lemon, juiced
½ cup extra virgin olive oil
Salt to taste
Cook the bacon util crispy while you prep the salad.
Finely shave brussel sprouts and add to a large bowl.
Make the dressing and toss with brussels sprouts.
Finely slice shallot and rinse in cold water. Chop the apples, chop the cooked bacon and pecans. Clean the pomegranates and add everything on top of the salad. Add the cheese and toss together to combine. Season with more salt to taste.
.
What are your family favorite dishes to make for the holidays?
.

#sponsored I’m partnering with @beefitswhatsfordinner and @texasroadhousebutchershop to bring you an easy Father’s Day grilled Ribeye Steaks with Mango, Avocado, Corn Salsa. Get the recipe and some great grilling tips ⬇️.
.
2 Ribeye Steaks
1 mango, diced
½ small red onion, finely diced
1 medium avocado, diced
1 jalapeno, finely diced
¼ cup cilantro, chopped (extra for serving)
2 ears corn, grilled (divided)
1 teaspoon olive oil, for corn
1 lime, juiced
Salt, to taste
Steak seasoning
.
1. Cut the mango, onion, avocado, jalapeno, cilantro and add to a bowl.
2. Oil the corn and set aside.
3. Pat them dry with a paper towel and season both sides with steak seasoning.
4. Preheat the grill to 500°F. Cut an onion in half, pierce with a fork and clean the grates (it adds flavor and cleans the grates at the same time).
5. Add the corn and steaks to the grill, close the lid and cook for 2 minutes. Flip and cook for 2 more minutes. Repeat for 2 more minutes per side. Check temperature and cook until desired doneness. Beef’s juicy texture is optimum when cooked to medium rare to medium doneness. Remove and let the steak rest for 5-10 minutes.
6. Remove the kernels off the corn and add to the bowl with salsa, squeeze the lime and add salt, toss to combine.
7. Cut the steaks across the grain to maximize tenderness and add to a serving platter. Cut the second corn into smaller pieces and add to the platter. Top with salsa and cilantro leaves and enjoy.
.
More tips on grilling the perfect steak:
➡️ Don’t overcrowd your grill - can cause uneven cooking.
➡️ Use a meat thermometer to test the temperature of steaks.
➡️ Rest your steak after cooking for 5-10 minutes, keep juices in.
➡️ Order your steaks for Father’s Day from TRButcherShop.com, and right now, get a free Beef. It’s What’s For Dinner. meat thermometer with purchase. ⬅️
.

#sponsored Recipe in caption ⬇️ Let’s make this Sautéed Pear Salad with a mustard dressing in partnership with @newseasonsmarket. I love shopping at my neighborhood New Seasons because they are an inviting, friendly, and inspiring grocery store with a strong focus on local and quality products. So let’s put together this fall salad with the ingredients I picked up from the store. It’s the perfect salad to serve at your next holiday get together!
.
Sautéed Pear Salad (serves 6)
.
6 slices bacon, sliced ¼ inch thick
4 firm Bosc pears, quartered, seeds removed
Kosher salt, to taste
1 tablespoon champagne vinegar
1 tablespoon whole grain mustard
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 tablespoon bacon fat
1 tablespoon honey
1/4 cup pecans, toasted
2 cups arugula
.
1. Cook the bacon until crispy, remove with a slotted spoon. Reserve bacon fat, leaving 1 tablespoon in the same pan.
2. Cut the pears into quarters and then sauté on medium heat in the bacon fat until golden brown on both cut sides. Set aside.
3. Toast the pecans in the same pan until golden brown.
4. Make the dressing by adding champagne vinegar, grainy mustard, olive oil, bacon fat, honey and salt, mix well to combine, taste for salt and adjust to liking.
5. In a serving platter add the arugula, pears, bacon, pecans and drizzle with the mustard dressing. Enjoy.
.
.

The Gin Drop. Try the Recipe ⬇️ below.
.
Makes 1 cocktail
.
2 oz empress gin @empress1908gin 
1/2 oz St. Germain @stgermaindrinks 
5 dashes Orange blossom water @cortasfood 
3/4 oz lemon juice, fresh or use @santacruzorganic 
1/2 oz agave @madhavafoods 
1 egg white
Dried lemon

Add all the ingredients to a cocktail shaker. Dry shake first. Then add ice and wet shake after. Pour into a coupe glass and enjoy with a dried lemon. Cheers!
.
.
